# Common Patterns

- `man x` will pull up the manual for command x. 

- Most programs take arguments as hyphenated inputs, a.ka. *flags*:

```
    ls -l 
```

- A lot of programs share these arguments:

    --help : brief usage instructions
    --version : version of the tool
    --verbose or -v : print more verbose output

- if `-` is used in place of a file, many programs will use the standard input.

